<HEADLINE>
FT  30 APR 93 / London Stock Exchange: Tiphook plunges
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PETER JOHN, STEVE THOMPSON and CHRISTOPHER PRICE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Container leasing group Tiphook was the market's biggest casualty yesterday,
the shares plunging more than 36 per cent at one point after a shock profits
warning.
At worst the shares touched 186p. They later stabilised to end a net 63 down
at 230p after heavy turnover of 7.4m.
Tiphook said its second-half profits would not match those of the first half
but the final dividend would be not less than 14.4p, indicating that the
dividend total would be 19.3p, against last year's 17.3p.
Analysts had previously been expecting Tiphook to achieve profits of some
Pounds 75m. After the warning estimates were chopped to around Pounds 58m.
</TEXT>
