FT  30 APR 93 / International Company News: Quebecor shrugs off recession as
profits triple
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GIBBENS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MONTREAL
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
QUEBECOR, the north American publishing, printing and forest products group,
tripled first-quarter profit in spite of the long recession and pressure on
advertising volumes.
Revenues were CDollars 671m (USDollars 527m), up 13 per cent, and net profit
was CDollars 15.4m, or 24 cents a share, up from CDollars 5.2m, or 8 cents,
