All segments improved, but most of the gains came from the fast-expanding
commercial printing business, now the second-biggest in north America
following the 1992 acquisition of Maxwell Graphics in the US for CDollars
510m.
Quebecor Printing, which has since gone public, is seeking acquisitions in
the western and south-western US and a beachhead in Europe.
