<HEADLINE>
FT  30 APR 93 / International Company News: McCaw reduces first-quarter loss
to Dollars 14m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MARTIN DICKSON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
MCCAW Cellular, the largest cellular telecommunications company in the US,
yesterday reported strong increases in revenue and cash flow from its
cellular operations, along with a much-reduced first quarter net loss of
just Dollars 14m, against Dollars 99m last year, writes Martin Dickson in
New York.
The fast-growing, heavily indebted business, which prefers analysts to focus
on cash flow from its cellular interests - income before depreciation and
amortisation and interest charges - said this figure totalled Dollars
163.6m, up from Dollars 113m.
Cellular revenues rose 31 per cent, from Dollars 276.6m to Dollars 363.1m.
Mr Craig McCaw, chairman, said the company was pleased with the continued
growth in subscriber revenues and operating cash flow.
