<TEXT>
WANG Laboratories, the US office computer systems company attempting to
emerge from bankruptcy proceedings, reported third-quarter net losses of
Dollars 87.2m, or 51 cents a share. These included estimated restructuring
charges of Dollars 75.8m related to a reorganisation plan.
Last year there was a first-quarter loss of Dollars 6.3m or 4 cents, when
Wang recorded a pre-tax gain of Dollars 29.4m from asset sales and changes
in its US pension plan.
Last month, Wang filed a restructuring plan with the bankruptcy court
describing its plans to end manufacturing operations and transform itself
into a software and services company.
For the nine-month period, the net loss was Dollars 153.4m or 90 cents a
share, against a net loss of Dollars 22.9m or 14 cents for the same period
last year.
