FT  30 APR 93 / Parliament and Politics: BR lease plan for rolling stock
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
MR ROGER Freeman, the public transport minister, said last night that
British Rail is to set up new companies to take over responsibility for all
its passenger rolling stock by April 1 next year.
The BR passenger fleet consists of 11,000 vehicles worth about Pounds 2bn
and the firms will lease vehicles to the new operators after privatisation.
Mr Freeman said: 'Our provisional view is that there should be three
rolling-stock companies.
'Wherever reasonably practicable franchisees should have more than one
potential source of supply for rolling stock in any particular market
segment,' he said.
