<HEADLINE>
FT  30 APR 93 / Parliament and Politics: Nelson warns on regulation
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE PACE of change in financial markets should not be allowed to get ahead
of the ability of managers and regulators to deal with it, Mr Anthony
Nelson, financial secretary to the Treasury, said yesterday.
Mr Nelson said at a conference organised by the Financial Times and the
Centre for the Study of Financial Innovation, a London-based group: 'I share
some of the CSFI's concern that at times the understanding of what is
happening in the financial community is in danger of lagging behind the
dynamics of the markets.'
The development of new financial products and the application of new
technology to the financial markets were strengths of London's international
financial centre, he said. But he added: 'We should think very carefully
about introducing new methods just because the technology is available.'
