<HEADLINE>
FT  30 APR 93 / Plan for rail fleet ownership
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
BRITISH RAIL has been told to set up three companies to take over ownership
of its Pounds 2bn fleet of passenger trains by next April as part of the
government's plans for rail privatisation.
The Department of Transport's intention is that the three companies will
lease the trains to the private-sector operators that win the franchises to
operate BR's passenger services.
</TEXT>
