FT  30 APR 93 / Pay freezes for Sheffield staff
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
MORE THAN half of pay deals reported this year by large engineering
companies in the Sheffield area have involved a wage freeze. In addition,
only one fifth of agreements involve increases above 3 per cent.
The figures, from the Sheffield's Engineering Employers Federation, cover 50
deals. One company negotiated a 10 per cent pay cut, 27 agreed a standstill
and three settled for under 2 per cent.
