<HEADLINE>
FT  30 APR 93 / Thames Water chief missing
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By BRONWEN MADDOX
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
SIR ROY Watts, chairman of Thames Water, has been missing since Tuesday
afternoon, police said last night as they appealled for information on his
whereabouts, Bronwen Maddox writes
Sir Roy, 67, - who is married with a son and two daughters, is understood to
suffer from Parkinson's disease.
Scotland Yard said officers had found his wallet, with cash and credit
cards, medication, and a pair of glasses in his Battersea flat in south
London, but they did not know if they were his only pair. He did not appear
to have extra clothes with him.
Thames Water said Sir Roy had been at work as normal on Tuesday at Thames's
central London headquarters.
His driver took him home at 2pm, since when he had had no contact with the
company or with his family in Oxford-shire.
</TEXT>
