<HEADLINE>
FT  29 APR 93 / Benefits awareness campaign launched
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A CAMPAIGN to inform unemployed people that they can still claim benefits if
they take upon a low-paid job was launched by the government yesterday.
Mr Peter Lilley, social security secretary, denied the move was cosmetic and
said the measures would help smooth the transition from unemployment into
work. About 1.7m unemployed people could still qualify for family credit
payments if they found work, he said.
