<HEADLINE>
FT  29 APR 93 / International Company News: Sweden to retain 25% of Celsius
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER BROWN-HUMES
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE Swedish government will retain a minority stake of 25 per cent in
Celsius Industries after this summer's privatisation of the country's
leading defence group.
A further 21 per cent of shares are to be taken up by four Swedish financial
institutions, while 43 per cent will be offered to domestic and foreign
investors, Celsius employees and the general public, according to the
government.
The remaining 11 per cent will be owned by Nobel Industries, which sold its
defence electronics activities to Celsius for SKr1.55bn (Dollars 209m) in
February. The shares have not been priced, but the group's value is
estimated at SKr3bn. The new structure ensures Celsius remains in Swedish
hands. There are no formal restrictions on foreign ownership but the state
retains the right to block hostile foreign bids.
</TEXT>
