FT  29 APR 93 / International Capital Markets: Horsham paper raises CDollars
125m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GIBBENS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MONTREAL
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
HORSHAM, a holding company controlled by Mr Peter Munk, chairman of
America's Barrick Resources, has raised about CDollars 125m by selling 8.5m
subordinated voting shares to underwriters at CDollars 14 7/8 each.
The shares will be distributed later in Canada, the US and Europe. Gordon
Capital leads the underwriting group.
Horsham owns 20 per cent of Barrick and 60 per cent of the US Clark Oil &amp;
Refining.
Perstorp, the Swedish speciality chemicals and plastics group, has agreed a
long-term credit facility with 16 international banks which will enable it
to borrow up to Dollars 150m over five years.
The multi-currency revolving facility was arranged by Credit Suisse First
Boston.
</TEXT>
