   By ROBERT GIBBENS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
CANADIAN Pacific Forest Products narrowed its losses in the first quarter
due to strong construction timber markets, larger newsprint and white paper
shipments, lower costs and a lower Canadian dollar.
The net loss was CDollars 64.8m (USDollars 51.8m), or Dollars 1.23 a share,
against a loss of Dollars 71.1m, or Dollars 1.47, a year earlier.
Sales were Dollars 450m, against Dollars 430m.
US newsprint prices east of the Rockies have gone up 10 per cent, but a
similar increase in the west has been postponed until midsummer.
White paper prices are strengthening again in the second quarter but pulp
demand and prices remain depressed.
