<HEADLINE>
FT  29 APR 93 / UK Company News: Eadie recovery and purchase
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A RETURN to trading profits and the dividend list in 1992, improved
prospects for the current year and expansion of its wheelchair business for
Pounds 1.12m cash were announced yesterday by Eadie Holdings, the specialist
engineer.
It is buying the business and certain assets of the mobility products
division, trading as Vessa, from BTR Industries. Some Pounds 600,000 of the
consideration will be raised by the placing of 2.54m shares at 24 1/2 p
each, underwritten by Allied Provincial Securities.
Group turnover rose 16 per cent to Pounds 23.3m (Pounds 20.1m), operating
profit was up 69 per cent at Pounds 1.22m (Pounds 720,000), and the pre-tax
balance worked through at Pounds 806,000, compared with Pounds 1.24m in 1991
which included gains on disposals and reorganisation of Pounds 1.3m.
The acquisitions - MCM in January and Cargo Controls in June - performed up
to expectations.
Earnings per share were 1.42p (losses 0.22p pre-exceptionals). The dividend
is 0.5p and is the first since 1989.
The improved trading of the latter part of the year has continued into 1993
and orders in most businesses were at higher levels.
Improved performance from existing divisions was expected.
</TEXT>
