<HEADLINE>
FT  29 APR 93 / UK Company News: Merlin cuts deficit to Pounds 652,000
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
MERLIN International Properties made further progress in eliminating trading
losses in the six months to December 31.
At the pre-tax level losses fell to Pounds 652,000, against Pounds 2.69m.
The outcome was achieved on turnover of Pounds 1.86m (Pounds 1.58m). Net
exceptional costs increased from Pounds 61,000 to Pounds 390,000 - which
represented the full cost of defending the compulsory purchase order on the
group's Manchester project.
Mr Peter Jevans, chairman, said there was evidence that market conditions
had ceased to worsen.
The company's attempts to achieve a financial restructuring and a relisting
had, as yet, borne no fruit, Mr Jevans said, but the directors were
confident of achieving a satisfactory end to this stalemate.
</TEXT>
