<HEADLINE>
FT  29 APR 93 / UK Company News: Fasteners side puts Reece in the red
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
REDUCED demand in its fasteners division left Reece, the cycles group which
also makes door panels and machinery for the ceramic industry, with pre-tax
losses of Pounds 662,000 for 1992 compared with restated pre-tax profits of
Pounds 373,000.
Operating losses from fasteners were Pounds 691,000 (Pounds 215,000
profits). Door panels suffered a Pounds 12,000 loss (Pounds 127,000 profits)
while profits in the cycle division fell by Pounds 78,000 to Pounds 258,000.
However, the company said that because of the continued growth of Probike
cycle sales, new warehousing facilities had been required and part of the
Solihull fastener depot had been released for that purpose.
Reece added that it had responded to the harsher economic environment by
cutting costs, rationalising operations and reducing working capital and
capital expenditure. Stock levels in fasteners had been reviewed and
additional provisions made where necessary.
Turnover slipped to Pounds 13.1m (Pounds 14.2m). Losses per share worked
through at 0.52p (0.43p earnings) and there is no dividend.
</TEXT>
