FT  29 APR 93 / UK Company News: Schroder Korea pays first dividend
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Schroder Korea Fund, a London-listed investment trust, had a net asset value
of Dollars 8.75 (568p) at December 31.
The trust, formed ahead of the opening of the Korean stock market to foreign
investors on January 3 1992, had attributable revenue of Dollars 119,000 for
the period from October 10 1991 - the date of incorporation - to
end-December.
Earnings emerged at 2.38 cents and a maiden dividend of 2 cents is
recommended.
