<HEADLINE>
FT  29 APR 93 / UK Company News: Murray Split Capital shows total return of
32%
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
OVER THE SIX months ended February 28 assets of Murray Split Capital Trust
increased 28 per cent for a total return, including dividends, of 32 per
cent.
That compared with a return of 30 per cent from the FT-A All-Share Index.
At the end of February net asset value per zero dividend preference share
was 118.8p (112.6p), per income share 50.2p (51.2p) and per capital share
172.2p (94.6p).
The performance reflected the strength of the high yield shares since
interest rates began to fall last autumn.
Total revenue was Pounds 580,000 in the six months and earnings worked
through at 4.23p. The second quarterly dividend is 2.65p to make 5.3p to
date. It is intended to maintain the annualised rate at 10.6p.
</TEXT>
