<HEADLINE>
FT  29 APR 93 / UK Company News: Plateau gets holders' assurance
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW BOLGER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
PLATEAU MINING, a natural resources group which is now a shell, has been
assured by shareholders owning more than 47 per cent of the company that
they do not intend to accept the Pounds 1.2m hostile bid from Kingstream
Resources, a small Australian exploration company.
Mr Donald Driver, chairman of Plateau, said: 'It is most unusual for
shareholders to come out against a bid at such an early stage. Major
shareholders have made their view clear about the Kingstream offer and other
shareholders will no doubt take the same view. Accordingly, Kingstream
should now give up gracefully and save everybody further costs.'
Kingstream launched its bid on April 13. Its offer of one share for every
eight Plateau values the latter at 2.62p, compared with the recent
suspension price of 3p.
Kingstream is reconsidering the terms after Plateau this week announced the
sale of a royalty interest to Delta Gold, an Australian group, for shares
worth more than Pounds 1.5m.
Guinness Mahon, adviser to Plateau, said the shell company had more than
Pounds 1m of net cash, as well as the Delta holding.
</TEXT>
